metadata.name: Telar #13
metadata.description:
Telar is a study about weaving.

Weaving is one of the oldest crafts in the world. It's been part of our history for almost 30,000 years. 

We are used as species to continuously see patterns generated by millions of binary decisions between colors. These patterns are part of the social DNA of almost every human culture, and their complex aesthetics generated by the most simple inputs are fascinating to me.

This piece, inspired by the mechanism of the Jacquard Loom — which is widely considered the first computer — uses combinations of colors, series, threading, treadling, and tie-up patterns to generate a unique 360-by-360-thread Telar ("loom" in Spanish). 

The algorithm called telar.js uses the hash to select some colors from preselected patterns and uses the input series to generate a base model with a starting pattern. After that, multiple iterations alter the model appending new tie-ups and modifying the threading or treadling and colors while keeping the design consistent. A resulting matrix containing each intersection then gets drawn on the screen resulting in a high-definition image the viewer can zoom in and see in detail. 

This algorithm takes too many pseudorandom trait values as its inputs that naming them was meaningless, so I would prefer collectors to focus on the subjective aesthetic values of the outputs. Therefore I am hiding the features for this collection.

Press 'S' on your keyboard to save it as a 36 megapixels print. Use the arrow keys to flip between the face and the back of the fabric.

metadata.name: Madone Solitaire #92
metadata.description:
“Madone Solitaire” is a series of generative drawings inspired by Japanese art and "Les fleurs du mal" by French author Charles Baudelaire.

Features:

- 30 color palettes 

- 3 background layers

- 3 different formats (square, portrait, and landscape)

-  50% chance of mountains 

Made with p5.js

Patricio Isaías, April 2022

metadata.name: Casuariiformes #95
metadata.description:
Casuariiformes are beautiful and colorful birds that give name to this project.

The intent of the project is to use geometry and colors to create beautiful compositions. Even in its own chaos, they primary shapes create a balance that make the composition appealing to human eye.

Note: if you get all six dice faces without repetition, DM me on Twitter as you will get a special airdrop!

metadata.name: Sprocket Factory #178
metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."

- Live renderer best viewed in Chrome.
- Press "P" to export an PNG raster image (10k resolution.)
- Press "S" to export an SVG vector.

metadata.name: Pixel Tunneling #167
metadata.description:
This is based on a technique I've used to create textured abstract art based by starting with a base design and applying millions of small mutations. Each design has a minimum of 3,000,000 mutations and as many as 10,000,000 mutations.

- Higher themes are more rare (25 max)
- Higher patterns are more rare (10 max)
- Chaos odds (medium=85%, low=10%, high=5%)
- Blend odds (medium=85%, low=10%, high=5%)

metadata.name: Euphonic #1086
metadata.description:
Euphonic is an exploration of the emergent visual properties that arise from placing layers of simple lines atop one another.

In general this effect is called the Moiré effect. This effect really feels best in the tactile - when you have a printed page and an acetate sheet. This piece attempts to recreate that tactile joy.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.

metadata.name: Colorfall #159
metadata.description:
My first attempt at a generative NFT. This started with an idea to create a grid of diagonal lines with the basic line function of p5js. I had discarded this idea until my friend said it looked like a waterfall of colors and he liked it, so I decided to mint it. After tweaking some parameters like colors and line thickness it produced some nice outputs.

I hope you will enjoy it. Free mint(unless you cant wait and want to pay =) plus 25% royalties for minters.

reserves for the collectors of my testnft on objkt, my friend CampendonkP and a few artists who I remembered who did free mints, like punevyr and JohnRising.

metadata.name: Refractions #269
metadata.description:
Refractions is a study of frequencies, harmonies and abstract representations of natural phenomena. 

It is an experiment of blending three colors to create integrated textural compositions.


Probabilities;

- 14 compositions with variations.

- 2 background color.

- 19 different base color palette (2 monochrome).

- 2 distinct textures with variations.

-  2 different alpha types; tangential & sinusoidal.

- Different edges.

- Several starting positions and styles (wavy or straight).


Made with p5.js

Ilgın İçözü, April 2022
@distcollective
